WEBVTT

00:01.601 --> 00:02.803
DOLE:
Previously on The Practice...

00:02.836 --> 00:04.170
BERLUTI: You were smoking crack

00:04.204 --> 00:05.672
with an eight-month baby.

00:05.705 --> 00:07.373
Please just get me out!

00:07.407 --> 00:08.909
BERLUTI: If I get you out,

00:08.942 --> 00:11.144
you go into rehab immediately.

00:11.177 --> 00:12.412
I promise.

00:12.445 --> 00:14.214
DOCTOR: The placental lining
started to come loose

00:14.247 --> 00:15.248
from the uterine wall,

00:15.281 --> 00:16.983
and there was cocaine
in her body.

00:17.017 --> 00:18.484
The baby?
DOCTOR: Little girl,

00:18.519 --> 00:19.686
three and a half pounds.

00:19.720 --> 00:22.022
I'm sorry, Jimmy.

00:22.055 --> 00:22.856
Okay.

00:24.290 --> 00:25.626
DONNELL: This is unbelievable!

00:25.659 --> 00:27.360
Two lovers
and they're both dead?

00:27.393 --> 00:28.795
What, you think just
because you got away

00:28.829 --> 00:30.063
with it last time,
you can get away

00:30.096 --> 00:31.932
with it whenever?
Yes.

00:31.965 --> 00:34.701
DOCTOR: He has a narcissistic
personality disorder.

00:34.735 --> 00:36.670
He commits a crime

00:36.703 --> 00:39.272
where it's impossible
not to convict him,

00:39.305 --> 00:41.074
and the game is still

00:41.107 --> 00:42.075
getting away with it.

00:42.108 --> 00:43.710
Well, win or lose.

00:43.744 --> 00:45.478
Won't this be fun?

00:45.512 --> 00:47.914
Were you trying to wrestle
the knife away,

00:47.948 --> 00:49.583
or were you trying
to kill him?

00:49.616 --> 00:51.417
It went into him
during the struggle.

00:51.451 --> 00:52.553
It went in by accident?

00:52.586 --> 00:54.387
How many ways can I say it?

00:54.420 --> 00:56.122
MAN: We find the defendant,
Joseph Heric,

00:56.156 --> 00:57.323
not guilty.

00:57.357 --> 01:00.293
(music playing)

01:05.632 --> 01:08.569
(horns honking)

01:12.205 --> 01:15.609
God, she's really
getting a personality.

01:15.642 --> 01:16.877
DONNELL: All right,
I'm out of here.

01:24.017 --> 01:26.452
Who'd you kill?

01:26.486 --> 01:28.722
Good to see you, too, Ellenor.

01:28.755 --> 01:30.090
Have you put on weight?

01:30.123 --> 01:31.958
We're busy, Joey.
Who'd you kill?

01:31.992 --> 01:33.159
Very cute.
Well, can't anybody say,

01:33.193 --> 01:36.262
"Hey, good to see you?"

01:36.296 --> 01:36.997
(baby chuckles)

01:37.030 --> 01:38.431
Whose is that?

01:38.464 --> 01:39.933
Mine. What are you doing here?

01:39.966 --> 01:41.802
You have a baby?

01:41.835 --> 01:43.604
DONNELL:
Joey, why are you here?

01:43.637 --> 01:45.471
Why don't we start by asking

01:45.506 --> 01:47.541
where I've been
for the last three years?

01:50.143 --> 01:51.712
Law school.

01:51.745 --> 01:52.746
Ta-da!

01:52.779 --> 01:54.548
Passed the bar in February.

01:54.581 --> 01:56.149
We're now all learned brothers.

01:56.182 --> 01:57.584
You're a lawyer?

01:57.618 --> 01:58.985
And a good one, so far.

01:59.019 --> 02:00.987
YOUNG: Wait, wait, wait.
You went to law school,

02:01.021 --> 02:01.988
took the bar exam?

02:02.022 --> 02:04.124
HERIC:
It was my therapist's idea.

02:04.157 --> 02:05.792
He thought one way
of weaning myself off

02:05.826 --> 02:07.728
of killing people
was to help others

02:07.761 --> 02:09.596
who did get away with it.

02:09.630 --> 02:10.496
I've got a case now

02:10.531 --> 02:11.364
that's why I'm here.

02:11.397 --> 02:13.099
Case? What kind of case?

02:13.133 --> 02:15.001
Homicide.

02:15.035 --> 02:17.103
I don't slum.

02:17.137 --> 02:19.372
The problem I'm having is this,

02:19.405 --> 02:21.675
I think the kid might
actually be innocent.

02:21.708 --> 02:23.409
And as good as I am,

02:23.443 --> 02:25.245
my conscience says
I should bring someone else

02:25.278 --> 02:26.980
on board with experience.

02:27.013 --> 02:28.381
FRUTT: So, in addition
to getting a law degree,

02:28.414 --> 02:29.816
you also picked up
a conscience?

02:29.850 --> 02:33.153
Drives like new,
hardly any miles on it.

02:33.186 --> 02:35.756
But seriously, Bobby,

02:35.789 --> 02:37.257
I'd never admit this publicly,

02:37.290 --> 02:39.526
but I could really
use some help.

02:39.560 --> 02:41.427
It starts tomorrow.

02:41.461 --> 02:42.428
Tomorrow?
HERIC: Yeah.

02:42.462 --> 02:43.597
I'm ready.
I can do this.

02:43.630 --> 02:44.798
And I could do it alone.

02:44.831 --> 02:46.332
I'm prepared to if I have to,

02:46.366 --> 02:49.169
but to be honest,

02:49.202 --> 02:51.437
with an innocent kid's life
on the line,

02:51.471 --> 02:54.140
believe it or not,
I don't want to.

02:54.174 --> 02:55.341
Come on, what do you say?

02:55.375 --> 02:58.311
You, me, Ellie,

02:58.344 --> 03:00.246
it'll be fun.

03:00.280 --> 03:02.115
Just like old times.

03:09.055 --> 03:12.526
(music playing)

03:58.038 --> 04:00.674
WASHINGTON:
You're actually helping him?

04:00.707 --> 04:02.208
And you?
FRUTT: Come on.

04:02.242 --> 04:04.277
I can't resist.
But he's a murderer.

04:04.310 --> 04:05.111
We only know that

04:05.145 --> 04:06.747
because we represented him.

04:06.780 --> 04:09.182
DOLE: Even so, we also know
he's clinically sick.

04:09.215 --> 04:10.383
Look, the ship has sailed.

04:10.416 --> 04:11.652
I'd said I'd help.

04:11.685 --> 04:13.787
Jimmy, it's someone
from Brigham Hospital.

04:16.255 --> 04:17.558
Jimmy Berluti.

04:20.160 --> 04:21.695
WOMAN (over PA):
Dr. Myser to x-ray.

04:21.728 --> 04:23.630
Dr. Myser to x-ray.

04:23.664 --> 04:27.100
(music playing)

04:27.133 --> 04:28.134
Hi.

04:29.235 --> 04:30.403
I'm sorry, Jimmy.

04:30.436 --> 04:31.872
Hey. Shh.

04:34.374 --> 04:35.942
This is Lucy Hatcher.

04:35.976 --> 04:37.578
She works with me.

04:37.611 --> 04:39.445
She also works
for Rape Crisis.

04:40.647 --> 04:43.049
I feel so stupid.

04:43.083 --> 04:45.451
What happened?

04:45.485 --> 04:50.356
You're gonna be mad, Jimmy.

04:50.390 --> 04:51.124
I'm still a...

04:51.157 --> 04:52.693
Prostitution?

04:55.796 --> 04:57.631
JENNIFER: It was a trick.

04:57.664 --> 04:58.732
He just went crazy.

04:58.765 --> 05:02.235
I don't--I'm so sorry.

05:02.268 --> 05:03.537
Where's your baby?

05:03.570 --> 05:05.506
She's with a friend.

05:05.539 --> 05:06.507
She's okay.

05:07.574 --> 05:09.976
So, what happened?

05:10.010 --> 05:11.745
One of your tricks
beat you up?

05:11.778 --> 05:14.681
He raped me.

05:14.715 --> 05:16.817
And then he beat me up.

05:16.850 --> 05:18.184
He raped you?

05:19.586 --> 05:22.155
The sex wasn't consensual?

05:22.188 --> 05:23.924
No.

05:23.957 --> 05:25.458
I mean, it probably
would have been.

05:25.491 --> 05:27.160
I mean,
we went to a room, too.

05:27.193 --> 05:29.696
But as soon as we got there,

05:29.730 --> 05:31.798
he just wigged out.

05:31.832 --> 05:34.334
It was like he had this thing
against hookers,

05:34.367 --> 05:35.736
like we were evil.

05:35.769 --> 05:38.204
I told him to get out,

05:38.238 --> 05:40.541
and he raped me.

05:40.574 --> 05:42.375
Do you think
you might recognize him

05:42.408 --> 05:45.145
if the police showed
you some photographs?

05:46.713 --> 05:48.314
He gave me his name.

05:51.852 --> 05:54.755
I told it to the police.

05:58.692 --> 06:00.927
ROLAND: The body
of Jean Homestead was found

06:00.961 --> 06:02.596
in an alley off
of Tremont Street,

06:02.629 --> 06:04.430
a deep gash in the back
of her head,

06:04.464 --> 06:08.134
the apparent victim
of a mugging.

06:08.168 --> 06:09.335
That's the way it looked

06:09.369 --> 06:11.171
because that's the way
that Daniel Carrington

06:11.204 --> 06:12.138
wanted it to look.

06:12.172 --> 06:14.074
But that is not the way
she died,

06:14.107 --> 06:15.108
ladies and gentlemen.

06:16.009 --> 06:19.312
The evidence
will show overwhelmingly,

06:19.345 --> 06:21.982
the defendant drove
to the victim's house,

06:22.015 --> 06:24.685
murdered Mrs. Homestead
in her bedroom,

06:24.718 --> 06:26.753
then drove her body back
into Boston

06:26.787 --> 06:29.690
and dumped her
into that alley.

06:29.723 --> 06:31.825
The evidence will establish
the defendant

06:31.858 --> 06:34.260
and the victim were
having an affair.

06:34.294 --> 06:36.897
And when the victim tried
to end the relationship,

06:36.930 --> 06:38.932
the defendant murdered her.

06:57.117 --> 06:59.720
The homicide rate
in this country,

06:59.753 --> 07:01.087
this city,
our city,

07:01.121 --> 07:03.857
the proud City of Boston,

07:03.890 --> 07:06.192
is starting to climb.

07:06.226 --> 07:08.562
And people,
people like me,

07:08.595 --> 07:10.931
you, are getting damn
sick of it.

07:12.298 --> 07:16.169
For one, I'm fed up
with exalting civil rights

07:16.202 --> 07:18.338
to the point
where the criminal

07:18.371 --> 07:21.508
enjoys more constitutional
privileges than we do.

07:21.542 --> 07:23.977
Enough already!

07:24.010 --> 07:27.013
If a person kills
another human being,

07:27.047 --> 07:28.915
I don't give a rat's ass

07:28.949 --> 07:31.017
whether he suffers
from schizophrenia,

07:31.051 --> 07:32.252
substance abuse,

07:32.285 --> 07:34.087
or an overbearing mother.

07:34.120 --> 07:36.122
I say put the son
of a bitch in jail.

07:36.156 --> 07:37.858
That's how I feel.

07:37.891 --> 07:40.594
It may be how some
of you feel, too.

07:40.627 --> 07:43.229
It's certainly how
the government feels,

07:43.263 --> 07:45.431
and I salute them for it.

07:47.100 --> 07:49.002
But,

07:49.035 --> 07:51.337
every once in a while,

07:51.371 --> 07:54.407
in their zeal,
their haste

07:54.440 --> 07:57.578
to make sure a murder
is avenged,

07:57.611 --> 07:59.012
they get it wrong,

07:59.045 --> 08:02.348
and they arrest
the wrong person.

08:02.382 --> 08:04.918
My heart goes out
to Jean Homestead's husband

08:04.951 --> 08:05.852
sitting there,

08:05.886 --> 08:07.453
and her son.

08:07.487 --> 08:10.156
We all wanna catch the person

08:10.190 --> 08:13.359
who killed Jean Homestead.

08:13.393 --> 08:14.961
But Daniel Carrington

08:14.995 --> 08:17.130
is not that person.

08:19.232 --> 08:20.701
They've arrested
the wrong man.

08:34.080 --> 08:36.049
Jimmy, the police
questioned the guy.

08:36.082 --> 08:37.317
What's his story?
Yeah.

08:37.350 --> 08:38.719
They went back
to her place,

08:38.751 --> 08:40.220
he didn't know
she was a hooker.

08:40.253 --> 08:43.056
After they had sex,
she announced she was,

08:43.089 --> 08:45.592
tried to extort him
for $10,000,

08:45.626 --> 08:46.860
he refused and left.

08:46.893 --> 08:49.663
And you believe that?
Jimmy, the examination

08:49.696 --> 08:51.832
didn't reveal
any vaginal bruising

08:51.865 --> 08:54.835
or tearing.
You see her face?

08:54.868 --> 08:56.402
You think she did
that to herself?

08:56.436 --> 08:59.239
I can't rule out
the possibility that she did.

08:59.272 --> 09:00.974
Why?
This is a hooker

09:01.007 --> 09:02.709
with a drug problem.

09:02.743 --> 09:06.046
Listen, even if
she's telling you the truth,

09:06.079 --> 09:08.782
a prostitute takes a man
to a room to have sex,

09:08.815 --> 09:11.885
then claims the sex
wasn't consensual.

09:13.319 --> 09:14.988
I'm not that good a DA.

09:17.791 --> 09:20.661
Both blows came to the back
of the skull.

09:20.694 --> 09:22.228
The second one,

09:22.262 --> 09:24.430
this one,
was fatal.

09:24.464 --> 09:26.032
It crushed both the skull

09:26.066 --> 09:27.834
and the brainstem.

09:27.868 --> 09:30.070
Death likely came instantly.

09:30.103 --> 09:31.672
ROLAND: And did you make
any other findings

09:31.705 --> 09:33.073
that you find significant?

09:33.106 --> 09:34.140
JOSH: Several.

09:34.174 --> 09:35.909
There were no other bruises,

09:35.942 --> 09:38.311
scratches,
no skin scrapings

09:38.344 --> 09:39.245
under her nails,

09:39.279 --> 09:40.914
no indication of a struggle.

09:40.947 --> 09:42.949
And what did that tell you?

09:42.983 --> 09:44.184
JOSH: Well, that
it's highly unlikely

09:44.217 --> 09:46.720
she was mugged,
or overpowered.

09:46.753 --> 09:49.422
Much more likely,
she was simply struck

09:49.455 --> 09:50.156
on the back of the head.

09:50.190 --> 09:51.925
ROLAND: Anything else?

09:51.958 --> 09:53.393
JOSH: We found small traces

09:53.426 --> 09:55.829
of semen in the vaginal area.

09:55.862 --> 09:58.965
We submitted samples
for DNA analysis.

09:58.999 --> 10:01.134
They were an exact
genetic match

10:01.167 --> 10:02.068
with the defendant.

10:02.102 --> 10:03.737
ROLAND: Thank you, Doctor.

10:08.775 --> 10:11.177
First of all, Doctor,

10:11.211 --> 10:13.179
let me applaud you
on your ability

10:13.213 --> 10:15.549
to crunch your testimony.

10:15.582 --> 10:17.217
So many experts,

10:17.250 --> 10:18.952
especially doctors,

10:18.985 --> 10:20.921
just rattle on
in such technical talk,

10:20.954 --> 10:23.924
it's either boring
or incomprehensible.

10:23.957 --> 10:25.559
I salute you, sir.

10:25.592 --> 10:26.760
Thank you.

10:26.793 --> 10:28.629
I probably shouldn't
be admitting this,

10:28.662 --> 10:30.764
but I can't take issue

10:30.797 --> 10:33.066
with a single thing you said.

10:33.099 --> 10:35.068
I agree with all of it.

10:35.101 --> 10:37.437
So, I'm going to sit down

10:37.470 --> 10:38.438
so we can move on.

10:42.175 --> 10:44.210
Oh, I'm sorry.

10:44.244 --> 10:45.078
There is one thing.

10:45.111 --> 10:48.181
It is possible for her
to be mugged

10:48.214 --> 10:50.116
and dragged
into the alleyway

10:50.150 --> 10:52.385
without showing
any physical signs,

10:52.418 --> 10:54.521
such as bruising
or fingernail scrapings?

10:54.555 --> 10:56.990
Yes, it's possible.

10:57.023 --> 10:58.158
Excellent. Thanks.

10:58.191 --> 11:01.427
Oh, oh, one other thing.

11:01.461 --> 11:04.765
If my client had had intercourse

11:04.798 --> 11:06.767
with the victim several hours

11:06.800 --> 11:09.235
before her death,

11:09.269 --> 11:11.471
semen evidence
could still be found,

11:11.505 --> 11:12.138
couldn't it?

11:12.172 --> 11:13.674
Yes.

11:13.707 --> 11:17.310
HERIC: So it's possible
my client

11:17.343 --> 11:20.113
and the victim had sex,

11:20.146 --> 11:22.749
she was later hit on the head

11:22.783 --> 11:25.318
and killed by somebody else?

11:25.351 --> 11:27.153
Your findings don't exclude
that possibility,

11:27.187 --> 11:28.655
do they, Doctor?

11:28.689 --> 11:29.322
No.

11:29.355 --> 11:31.091
Thank you.

11:39.733 --> 11:40.534
How'd I do?

11:44.771 --> 11:46.006
He raped me.

11:46.039 --> 11:47.974
And it would be your word
against his.

11:49.042 --> 11:50.844
Do you know who he is?

11:50.877 --> 11:51.712
Russell Mathis.

11:51.745 --> 11:55.248
He's a very prominent Lawyer.

11:55.281 --> 11:58.451
He would be perceived
to be more credible

11:58.484 --> 12:01.555
than a hooker
with a drug history.

12:01.588 --> 12:04.891
Look, I'm your friend.

12:04.925 --> 12:07.427
There's nothing
to be done here.

12:07.460 --> 12:09.763
YOUNG: Maybe not criminally.

12:09.796 --> 12:12.599
I would think
Mr. Mathis would like us

12:12.633 --> 12:14.367
to go away without any noise.

12:14.400 --> 12:17.971
(music playing)

12:18.004 --> 12:20.607
I'll go pay him a visit, Jimmy.

12:25.979 --> 12:28.615
JEAN (over recording):
I'm ending it now, Danny.

12:28.649 --> 12:30.083
I can't see you anymore.

12:30.116 --> 12:32.118
I'm married,
and the truth is,

12:32.152 --> 12:34.220
you're beginning
to frighten me a little.

12:34.254 --> 12:37.558
I just need you to stay away.

12:38.592 --> 12:41.094
That was identified
as the voice of the victim?

12:41.127 --> 12:43.196
Identified
by her husband, yes.

12:43.229 --> 12:45.265
ROLAND: Where was this message
found, Detective?

12:45.298 --> 12:47.367
On the defendant's voicemail,

12:47.400 --> 12:48.535
recorded six minutes

12:48.569 --> 12:50.571
past 9:00 on January 17th.

12:50.604 --> 12:52.973
ROLAND: And according
to the coroner's findings,

12:53.006 --> 12:54.875
when did Mrs. Homestead die?

12:54.908 --> 12:56.442
Her body temperature indicated

12:56.476 --> 12:58.779
that she died about 10:00 PM
that same night.

12:58.812 --> 13:00.146
Did you make any findings

13:00.180 --> 13:02.048
as to where she died,
Detective?

13:02.082 --> 13:04.117
Our conclusion
was that she died

13:04.150 --> 13:05.351
in her own bedroom.

13:05.385 --> 13:06.987
There were microscopic
blood splatterings

13:07.020 --> 13:08.889
on her bedpost
as well as the carpet.

13:08.922 --> 13:11.925
The blood matched up
genetically to the victim.

13:11.958 --> 13:13.960
We believe
she was killed there

13:13.994 --> 13:14.961
and then moved.

13:14.995 --> 13:16.930
Any other evidence
lead you to this?

13:16.963 --> 13:19.499
We also found microscopic
blood splatterings

13:19.533 --> 13:20.801
in the defendant's car,

13:20.834 --> 13:23.537
blood that also belonged
to the victim.

13:23.570 --> 13:24.938
Thank you, Detective.

13:31.512 --> 13:33.714
Well, things really look bleak

13:33.747 --> 13:35.048
for our side,
don't they?

13:37.183 --> 13:39.252
Now, I imagine

13:39.285 --> 13:41.487
that's why
you arrested my client.

13:41.522 --> 13:43.123
The phone message,

13:43.156 --> 13:45.025
the blood splatterings,

13:45.058 --> 13:46.192
the affair--

13:48.061 --> 13:49.796
well, come to think of it,

13:49.830 --> 13:50.797
that would be it,
wouldn't it?

13:50.831 --> 13:53.099
I mean, that's your entire case,

13:53.133 --> 13:55.836
blood, phone message,
and affair.

13:55.869 --> 13:56.870
Right, Detective?

13:56.903 --> 13:58.004
And his semen.

13:58.038 --> 13:59.640
Right. Well,
I was sort of including

13:59.673 --> 14:00.541
that with "affair."

14:02.108 --> 14:03.276
Any weapon?

14:03.309 --> 14:04.511
No.

14:04.545 --> 14:06.112
Any evidence,

14:06.146 --> 14:07.748
physical, forensic,

14:07.781 --> 14:09.516
testimonial that my client

14:09.550 --> 14:11.217
was in the victim's bedroom
that night?

14:11.251 --> 14:12.586
His semen.

14:12.619 --> 14:13.787
Well, the coroner
has already admitted

14:13.820 --> 14:15.856
that they could
have made love earlier,

14:15.889 --> 14:17.457
maybe even someplace else.

14:17.490 --> 14:20.026
Do you disagree with
the coroner on that, Detective?

14:20.060 --> 14:21.862
No.
HERIC: And this blood

14:21.895 --> 14:23.096
you're talking about,

14:23.129 --> 14:25.699
"microscopic," you said.

14:25.732 --> 14:26.667
So, if we took all this blood

14:26.700 --> 14:27.668
and pooled it together,

14:27.701 --> 14:29.503
the blood you found
both in her bedroom

14:29.536 --> 14:31.505
and my client's car,

14:31.538 --> 14:33.974
more or less than

14:34.007 --> 14:36.176
